    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.35b.13"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">13</fw>
                    
                <fw type="imprint">  
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>Seal of the United States of America</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">EMBASSY OF THE 
                        <lb/>
                    UNITED STATES OF AMERICA</hi> 
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>July 31, 1971</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska</addrLine>
                        <addrLine><hi rend="caps">U.S.A.</hi></addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear John:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Many thanks for your note with regard to my recent leg injury and for your previous note with respect to publication matters in which you are presently involved.</p>
                    
                <p>After two weeks in the hospital--during which time they operated on me and inserted a steel plate and six horrible-looking big screws--and two weeks at home with my leg in a cast, I must say that I am feeling well. I believe the leg is healing satisfactorily and I am conducting business more or less as usual.</p> 
                
                <p>Monday, August 2, the doctor will remove the cast, inspect my leg, exray it, and I should then have a report on how I stand to date. He does tell me that I must not walk on the leg until at least September 9. This creates some problems for Elizabeth and me as we plan to leave here on September 17 for Washington where I will be in consultation for a week in the State Department. Then we will proceed to Nebraska.</p> 
                
                <p>We want to enjoy the unparalleled Indian summer of the Midwest, see old friends, learn what home folks are thinking about the state of the nation and the world, see the world series on television, sample Nebraska football offerings--high school, college, and university--and enjoy some good Nebraska cooking. We will also be doing some moving around the States to visit relatives.</p>
                    
                <p>We are looking forward to being in Wayne for Homecoming and for Wayne State Foundation meetings. In that connection, I wonder if you will permit me the privilege of proposing you as a Trustee of the Foundation. You would indeed do us honor if you would serve in that capacity, and I think it would be interesting to have a father-daughter combination. Hilda is a top-flight Trustee and I know that John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt would be the same.</p> 
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.35b.14"/>
                    
                <fw type="authorial">     
                    Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt 
                    Page 2
                    <date>July 31, 1971</date>
                </fw>
                <fw type="curatorial">14</fw>
                
                <p>I hope that all of your publication efforts meet with your desires and that your autobiographical work moves along in a manner which pleases you. I am certainly looking forward to having an opportunity to read it.</p> 
                
                <p>Elizabeth and I hope that your program will eventuate in such a way that you can drop in on us. If you cannot come this summer, we hope to see you in Wayne in October and here on some other occasion.</p>
                
                <p>Many thanks for your good wishes.</p> 
                
                <p>Kindest personal regards.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Val</signed>
                    <signed>Val Peterson</signed> 
                    
                    <note>VP:sat</note> 
                </closer>
                    
            </div1>
